00:08:31.711 --> 00:08:35.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When I said I'd kill you,
it wasn't just a figure of speech.

136
00:08:35.781 --> 00:08:37.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ajins can die.

137
00:08:37.917 --> 00:08:40.019  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Ugh. Now he's done it
-Huh?

138
00:08:41.087 --> 00:08:44.223  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Sato]
It depends on how you define death, but...

139
00:08:45.291 --> 00:08:50.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
when Ajins die, pieces of their body that
have been severed join back together...

140
00:08:51.631 --> 00:08:55.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with the largest piece
that still remains intact.

141
00:08:55.635 --> 00:08:58.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But if they're too far,
they're just remade.

142
00:08:58.938 --> 00:09:00.606  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What if it's your head?

143
00:09:01.274 --> 00:09:06.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Hmm. I promise you...
I am going to cut off your head.

144
00:09:10.650 --> 00:09:15.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Then I'll pick up that head,</i>
<i>and I will force you to watch...</i>

145
00:09:15.655 --> 00:09:19.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>until a new one is ultimately regenerated.</i>

146
00:09:19.792 --> 00:09:26.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The question is, is the brain that remains
inside your head actually yours?

147
00:09:27.867 --> 00:09:29.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Here you are.

148
00:09:29.769 --> 00:09:33.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Get ready. It's over for you.

149
00:09:34.106 --> 00:09:35.675  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

150
00:09:35.841 --> 00:09:41.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're going to regret shooting me,
so much so that it kills you.

151
00:09:42.081 --> 00:09:43.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

152
00:09:44.083 --> 00:09:45.284  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nagai, Kei...

153
00:09:46.686 --> 00:09:48.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you don't have to help us.

154
00:09:48.354 --> 00:09:49.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Huh?
-What?

155
00:09:56.596 --> 00:09:57.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will, though.

156
00:09:59.165 --> 00:10:00.333  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll get you out.

157
00:10:01.701 --> 00:10:03.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what I should do...

158
00:10:03.903 --> 00:10:04.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I guess.

159
00:10:13.145 --> 00:10:14.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

160
00:10:14.714 --> 00:10:16.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Get the back of his neck, his spinal cord.</i>

161
00:10:16.682 --> 00:10:19.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>If I do it right, I can cut all the nerves</i>
<i>without killing him.</i>

162
00:10:20.152 --> 00:10:21.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps, then grunts]

163
00:10:21.621 --> 00:10:23.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato laughing]

164
00:10:24.023 --> 00:10:25.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both grunt]

165
00:10:30.796 --> 00:10:32.231  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[yells]

166
00:10:43.376 --> 00:10:44.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you doing?

167
00:10:44.844 --> 00:10:45.978  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We promised him!

168
00:10:46.879 --> 00:10:49.415  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Aiding and abetting his flight?
This one's all on you!

169
00:10:50.116 --> 00:10:53.185  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groaning]

170
00:10:54.120 --> 00:10:55.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] I shouldn't have bothered.

171
00:10:57.923 --> 00:11:00.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn! Why is this happening to me?

172
00:11:08.134 --> 00:11:10.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is--? What's that?

173
00:11:15.174 --> 00:11:17.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is this? It's so big.

174
00:11:20.813 --> 00:11:22.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

175
00:11:25.851 --> 00:11:26.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

176
00:11:28.754 --> 00:11:30.723  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei IBM] If that happens...

177
00:11:31.991 --> 00:11:32.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll kill them.

178
00:11:34.160 --> 00:11:35.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato] <i>So, this is Nagai's.</i>

179
00:11:36.829 --> 00:11:38.464  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Such a plain shape.</i>

180
00:11:42.401 --> 00:11:45.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kei IBM]
How about just cutting off their arms?

181
00:11:46.105 --> 00:11:46.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato grunts]

182
00:11:47.339 --> 00:11:51.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Sato] <i>It's true that the black ghosts</i>
<i>sometimes repeat words</i>

183
00:11:51.277 --> 00:11:53.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>or wander around without orders.</i>

184
00:11:54.847 --> 00:11:55.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

185
00:11:57.216 --> 00:11:59.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[yells]

186
00:12:03.055 --> 00:12:05.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Sato]
<i>But this one's way too independent.</i>

187
00:12:07.359 --> 00:12:09.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei IBM] Sorry to cause so much trouble.

188
00:12:12.064 --> 00:12:15.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kishi] <i>Invisible people</i>
<i>made of an unknown substance?</i>

189
00:12:15.935 --> 00:12:20.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And just what exactly does that have to do
with Ajins not dying?

190
00:12:20.506 --> 00:12:23.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Ogura] Tell me this.
Why do people eat oranges?

191
00:12:23.476 --> 00:12:24.343  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

192
00:12:24.910 --> 00:12:28.414  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Serves you right.
Thanks to that thing I got away

193
00:12:28.781 --> 00:12:30.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[panting]

194
00:12:31.317 --> 00:12:35.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Ogura] People are incapable
of generating vitamin C on their own.

195
00:12:35.821 --> 00:12:38.791  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, they have to get it through fruits
and other sources.

196
00:12:39.191 --> 00:12:41.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The black ghost. [grunts]

197
00:12:41.393 --> 00:12:43.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, Ajins can summon those.

198
00:12:43.462 --> 00:12:45.998  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Ogura]<i> Ajins who die of malnutrition</i>

199
00:12:46.065 --> 00:12:49.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>can even produce their own vitamins</i>
<i>when they regenerate.</i>

200
00:12:50.002 --> 00:12:53.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Unh. What has that got to do
with not dying?

201
00:12:57.209 --> 00:13:02.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, it has to be related to their ability
to generate an unknown substance.

202
00:13:02.248 --> 00:13:04.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

203
00:13:08.087 --> 00:13:10.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[panting]

204
00:13:18.030 --> 00:13:18.898  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is it?

205
00:13:19.798 --> 00:13:21.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm gonna hide out in this room.

206
00:13:21.834 --> 00:13:25.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't you realize that the killer
might be coming after us as well?

207
00:13:26.172 --> 00:13:29.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasping]

208
00:13:38.150 --> 00:13:40.119  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[breathing nervously]

209
00:13:49.228 --> 00:13:50.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right. [gasps]

210
00:13:51.397 --> 00:13:53.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[metal grinding, then Kondo gasps]

211
00:13:55.601 --> 00:13:57.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps] What?

212
00:14:01.073 --> 00:14:03.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato IBM] Oh, you can see it?

213
00:14:05.110 --> 00:14:09.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sometimes people can see these, when
there's a strong feeling directed at them.

214
00:14:10.382 --> 00:14:12.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Like the urge to kill, for example.

215
00:14:12.551 --> 00:14:15.020  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[whimpering]

216
00:14:15.087 --> 00:14:17.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please, don't!

217
00:14:18.190 --> 00:14:20.059  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato IBM] Sorry, that won't work.

218
00:14:20.492 --> 00:14:24.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
To tell the truth, I rather enjoy killing.

219
00:14:24.563 --> 00:14:26.332  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kondo gasping]

220
00:14:28.334 --> 00:14:31.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kondo screaming]

221
00:14:35.307 --> 00:14:36.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[panting]

222
00:14:37.243 --> 00:14:38.444  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nomura] Nagai, over here!

223
00:14:44.216 --> 00:14:45.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why are you still here?

224
00:14:45.618 --> 00:14:46.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The fire escape chute.

225
00:14:47.386 --> 00:14:48.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I had to show you how to use it.

226
00:14:48.921 --> 00:14:52.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] Oh, no, I won't need that.

227
00:14:52.291 --> 00:14:53.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, right.

228
00:14:56.528 --> 00:14:59.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wonder if I would die from this height.

229
00:15:00.232 --> 00:15:03.102  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But that's not the real reason
why I waited.

230
00:15:03.302 --> 00:15:04.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

231
00:15:04.536 --> 00:15:08.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Once we get down,
I can drive you somewhere in my car.

232
00:15:09.942 --> 00:15:12.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Huh?
-I told myself it was just my job,

233
00:15:12.978 --> 00:15:15.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but we really did
such cruel things to you.

234
00:15:15.614 --> 00:15:18.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's one more thing
I wanted to reassure you about.

235
00:15:19.385 --> 00:15:21.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Listen, you're still you.

236
00:15:22.621 --> 00:15:25.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We never once beheaded you
during the experiments,

237
00:15:25.357 --> 00:15:28.027  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and no brain cells were left
at the truck accident site either.

238
00:15:28.427 --> 00:15:29.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I just wanted you to know that.

239
00:15:30.996 --> 00:15:34.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How is it that you're able to worry
about others?

240
00:15:34.466 --> 00:15:35.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nomura] Hmm?

241
00:15:36.168 --> 00:15:38.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Can you actually understand
all their pain?

242
00:15:39.705 --> 00:15:43.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's just I've never really worried
about anyone else before.

243
00:15:44.209 --> 00:15:47.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Sato]
<i>Nagai, you really are quite interesting.</i>

244
00:15:48.013 --> 00:15:51.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Including that personality</i>
<i>your sister talked about.</i>

245
00:15:56.388 --> 00:15:58.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Araki]
What kind of person your brother is.

246
00:15:59.091 --> 00:16:01.460  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, that's what those two asked you?

247
00:16:02.261 --> 00:16:03.128  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah.

248
00:16:03.696 --> 00:16:05.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And so, what did you say?

249
00:16:07.533 --> 00:16:08.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My brother is...

250
00:16:10.569 --> 00:16:11.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>a jerk.</i>

251
00:16:12.071 --> 00:16:13.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunshot, then Kei grunts]

252
00:16:13.305 --> 00:16:14.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei whimpers]

253
00:16:14.473 --> 00:16:16.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The wind's blowing hard.

254
00:16:16.241 --> 00:16:17.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nomura] Hide.

255
00:16:21.213 --> 00:16:22.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both grunt]

256
00:16:25.250 --> 00:16:26.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Araki]<i> A jerk, huh?</i>

257
00:16:26.719 --> 00:16:28.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ha-ha-ha. That's uh--

258
00:16:28.587 --> 00:16:29.455  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He is.

259
00:16:32.725 --> 00:16:37.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My brother is actually very logical
and completely cold.

260
00:16:39.298 --> 00:16:40.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's just...

261
00:16:41.400 --> 00:16:42.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>what he's like.</i>

262
00:16:43.769 --> 00:16:44.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

263
00:16:44.770 --> 00:16:46.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kei] <i>If he's dead,</i>
<i>I can't help him anymore.</i>

264
00:16:48.307 --> 00:16:49.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>So, that's the shortest way</i>

265
00:16:50.309 --> 00:16:51.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>But this body...</i>

266
00:16:54.013 --> 00:16:55.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[gunshots]
[Kei grunting]

267
00:16:56.448 --> 00:16:57.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

268
00:16:58.617 --> 00:17:00.319  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm, too bad.

269
00:17:00.586 --> 00:17:01.787  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Out of bullets.

270
00:17:02.388 --> 00:17:03.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

271
00:17:03.622 --> 00:17:04.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nomura coughs]

272
00:17:05.524 --> 00:17:06.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[coughing and gasping]

273
00:17:07.092 --> 00:17:08.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Wait, he's still alive?

274
00:17:09.094 --> 00:17:11.797  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is the final stage, Nagai.

275
00:17:12.564 --> 00:17:15.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting] Damn it!

276
00:17:18.037 --> 00:17:20.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

277
00:17:21.740 --> 00:17:25.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
